Create and Manage Flows

You can customize the provided flows to meet your needs and add quick actions.

Several flows for common service requests in retail banking and insurance are included with the Lightning Flow for Financial Services Cloud package.

The flows in the package are installed as standard flow templates. You can clone a template and customize it to suit your business processes.

Give users easy access to a flow by creating a quick action. When you add the quick action to the Person Account page layout, users can launch the flow from person account record pages.

Add the quick actions to the Person Account page layout so that they appear in the action menu on the highlights panel on Person Account record pages.

A flow’s output is a case record and a JSON string. The JSON string contains the key pieces of information that are provided during the execution of the flow.

Files uploaded during a flow are attached to the case record that the flow creates. You can choose which file types you want to allow.

For disputed transactions, you can set an approval limit for service reps. If a disputed transaction amount is within the approval limit, the Dispute Transactions flow marks the resulting case as Closed.

The Send Documents flow has a list of commonly used documents. You can add more documents to the list.

Review these points to understand how the provided flows work:

*   Create and manage flows
*   Customize prepackaged flows
*   Add quick actions to person account page layout
*   View a flow’s output
*   Restrict file types to upload in a flow
*   Set an approval limit for disputed transactions
*   Add documents to the Send Documents flow
title: Customizing and Managing Flows in Financial Services Cloud
